Prothorax (
Fig. 2 b
): in dorsal view brown with pale sides, anterior lobe with anterior margin smooth. In lateral view propleuron dark with prominent lobes. Pterothorax: (
Fig. 2 c
) largely brown with metepisternum and metepimeron pale. Mesostigmal plate without hairs. Middorsal carina brown. Mesepisternum with a complete narrow yellow antehumeral stripe. Mesinfraepisternum brown, becoming darker next to mesothoracic suture and reddish towards mesocoxa. Mesepimeron entirely brown. Metinfraepisternum pale. Metepisternum pale with a wide dark brown stripe on metapleural suture. Metepimeron largely pale, in ventral view venter of thorax completely yellow.

Fw ( 27.2mm ): (
Fig. 2 d
): two complete Ax, 21 Px, IR 2 arising little after subnodus, RP 2 arising between seventh and eighth Px, RP 3–4 arising little before subnodus; CUP close to first complete Ax. CUA arising close to second Ax; MA arising little after second Ax; IR 1 arising close to ninth or tenth Px.

Hw ( 27mm ) (
Fig. 2 e
) two complete Ax, 19 Px, RP 2 arising between fifth and sixth Px, RP 3–4 arising before subnodus, IR 2 arising a little after subnodus; IR 1 arising at eighth Px.

Abdomen ( 35 mm , including appendages): abdominal segments largely brown, with basal pale ring in all segments. Dorsally, posterior margin of S 10 medially recessed (
Fig. 2 f
), cerci brown, in dorsal view slightly curved inwards, with rounded and slightly flattened tips, external margin armed with small spines, distal region with an excavation, in lateral view directed medio-ventrally and wide at base (
Fig. 2 f
); paraprocts elongate, surpassing length of cercus, wide at base, with dorsal margin sclerotized and prominent, and with slender and rounded tips. In lateral view directed upwards (
Fig. 2g
).

Genital ligula : inner fold well developed; shaft sclerotized along middle region, armed with 10–15 short and thin spurs; apical segment membranous, tip slightly concave with bilobulate long trumpet-shaped extensions, surpassing middle region of ligula in lateral view (
Fig. 2 h, i
).

Female allotype. Coloration and wing venation as in male. IR 1 arising at eighth Px in FW, at seventh Px in HW. Gonapophyses in dorsal view with distinctive, pale, scarcely sclerotized region between end of S 7 and anterior margin of S 8 ; in lateral view tip of ovipositor not surpassing cercus, armed with minute spines ventrally (
Fig. 2 j, k
); vulvar spine absent.
